## Troubleshooting

| Issue | Solution |
|-------|----------|
| Kernel fails to start (timeout) | Reload VS Code window. The WMI patch in sitecustomize.py may be loading. Retry. |
| "Could not render content" on training cells | Clear notebook outputs and rerun the cell. Widget state will regenerate. |
| CUDA not available | Verify PyTorch installation includes CUDA. Run `python -c "import torch; print(torch.cuda.is_available())"`. Reinstall if False. |
| Data path errors | Ensure `.env` file exists and `DATASET_PATH` points to the NIH dataset root with `Data_Entry_2017.csv`. |
| Out of memory (OOM) | Reduce BATCH_SIZE in config.py (try 32 or 16). |
| Models save to wrong directory | Check `outputs/checkpoints/` and `outputs/models/` ownership and disk space. |

